cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.IR. 

The paper deals with action recognition in videos, which is a subfield of computer vision. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also introduces a new model based on deep learning, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as well. The dataset used in the paper is collected from YouTube videos, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia). The paper also discusses the performance of different architectures, which could be related to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
